8- Internal Structure of the Heart 

Sunday, May 28, 2017 

9:55 PM 

Identify on the right atrium: The right auricle, crista terminalis, fossa ovalis, opening of the coronary sinus, pectinate muscles, tricuspid valve 

 

 

 

Identify on the right ventricle: tricuspid valve and orifice, papillary muscles, chordae tendineae, septomarginal trabeculae, pulmonary trunk, pulmonary semilunar valve 

Identify on the left atrium: pulmonary veins, fossa ovalis, left auricle, mitral orifice and valve 

Identify on the left ventricle: mitral orifice, chordae tendineae, trabeculae carneae, aortic semilunar valve and nodule, right and left coronary arteries, muscular and membranous parts of the interventricular septum
